\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Were your parents church goers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
No I don't they were very interested but they saw that we were. My mother used to go to church of course on a Sunday morning and then she got attached to the West London mission and became quite a friend there
, the Reverend James Rattenbury and so I left the Church of England more or less a none conformist as the service appealed to me. I don't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4339284\charrsid4274267 go to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267  church like I used to I have got the time, I can't get along on account of my arthritis. That was very interesting all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Had your parents any papers or magazines?
