\insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 \} they reminded me of her. She really dominated us. We all stood in awe of her and you did your best work, there is no question of anything will do like the youngsters of today. No I liked milliner
y I always wanted to be a milliner and of course it gave me a good training. When I married my husband, we fell on rather hard times and then I had to become a tailoress and I got into the tailoring trade when I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10751506\charrsid4274267 twenty three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267  and I have been attached to it ever since. I only do part time now. I don't do very much now, I only do }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10751506\charrsid4274267 four }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
afternoons a week now. It is a strain for my eyes or my hands and I take things much easier. At home on a Friday afternoon ..... I mean it was unheard of years ago. We used t
o work with my husband. Mr. Garth used to come and inspect the property ................ I was a poor little tailoress. Park Mews. My home was always clean and tidy and always has been. Anybody could come and I used to work until 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 10}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}10 o'clock{\*\xmlclose} and I was never finished until {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 11}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}11 o'clock{\*\xmlclose}
. We worked Sundays and we only went away one week every year because tailoring is a sweaty trade. If I don't work I don't get paid. I go in yesterday afternoon I do four hours I get paid for the hours. You don't get paid for sick
ness or anything like that, it is a sweated trade. It was a very hard trade until a few years ago. I have a very well to do brother, he is very kind and he said I was to stop the mornings and he would pay me what I was earning and since January I have bee
n
 at home most mornings except one morning a week when I go to see my boys, they look so forward to seeing me that it is very pleasant to be busy. I have always been busy all my life. I have always had to work all my life and I couldn't be at home in this 
s
mall flat all day long. I work four afternoons that's as much as I want. I have certainly worked very hard all my life. .......... She used to come up now and again, it was a large flat and a very dirty flat, there was an engineering workshop underneath. 
I
 did have some work to do, nobody knows what I cleaned in that flat on my hands and knees. Mrs. Hearne came round and had a cup of tea. She always said it was so clean and tidy. I told them I couldn't be untidy. We had our workshop in the Mews and before 
t
hat we were in Marylebone and had a workshop there. It makes a lot of dirt tailoring and a lot of work. Because we worked for some famous people, dukes and lords and all, famous people Clark Gable, Robert Taylor we made all their clothes. I have never bee
n
 much to fuss about for myself. When they've come up my hair's been tidy but I used to say never mind what I look like but at least things were reasonable............... He used to come and he had never seen a gentleman working before. He had to come once
 
when the lease had run out at No. 11 and he came up and said there's a lot to be done to this house. Then he came to the workroom and we really shouldn't work them, they really don't allow you to work, however, it was our tenancy and they could say nothin
g about it. He came in the afternoon and I said I was just about to make a cup of tea would you like. He said I'd love it. It has been most interesting. He saw Charlie working on I think it was a golf champion's coat or what was it, it was a famous }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15276983\charrsid4274267 person\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
 coat. And this person said I would really like you to make me a coat and Charlie said we were very busy he said we work for shops he said and we are busy but if I can I would. He came up later on and Charlie said he would be delighted to do it. Later on 
w
e heard who he was. There you were talking to him, said Charlie. When he said who he was I said well sir I always say this, I am poor, honest and respectable. that was my epitaph. He had a naughty little glint in his eye and he would say now let me see yo
u
 are poor, honest and respectable and he used to love me say it. Poor, honest and respectable. Well there I am I said. No came up quite a number of time to see and Charlie and during the war time we had a little fire in our work room and the bottom fell o
u
t of it and as luck would have it he came up and I called him into our work room and I said Mr. Gardener look at this. Oh he said my goodness he said what a mess it has made................... You must have it put right. Well within a week he had a new fi
r
eplace put in............ as I say they have all been very, very kind to me in every shape and form. Any little jobs that perhaps wanted doing., although they couldn't expect us to do it. Our living room had an old fashioned grate it was awful well it was
 
old property. I happened to show him one day I said we couldn't use it very much and he said we are hoping to put new fireplace in but I think I will give you priority. We had a new fireplace right away. I thought it was simply lovely. I said to him one s
 
day if we bought the paper I said my husband was very busy at the time, I said do you think Mr. Gardener you could paper the room and he said I will put it down and he did. We bought the paper and he papered the room. Now it was a concession, on the lease
 
we had to do all interior decoration but I thought that was very nice. They have always been very charming to us .................... My husband used to say you've got a sore throat and I would say it is natural. Can you stay and have a cup of tea if I ma
ke one dear.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15276983\charrsid4274267 You said you had one brother about eight years younger.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Seven years, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 And what was the relationship between you and the years? How much older or younger was the other one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well, I'm, the elder of the family and he's six or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751506\charrsid4274267 seven }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 years younger than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 And the other one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes, he died last year. He was 5 years younger than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Do you know, roughly speaking, how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I think he must have been about 28, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Do you know, before he went into business if he had any other job, or had he always been in business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
No, I think he worked for someone - I know he went to Paris for some time to study, he was an ambitious man - to study French when he opened a littl
e business in Paris, and then he came over here, and saved a little money, and lived in High St., Marylebone, for what I can remember, or what I've been told, and then got his own 2 or 3 businesses in London.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 But he didn't have any other kind of way of earning a living that you know of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, no, he was a hairdresser.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did he do that all his working life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Do you know how old your mother was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I think they were very much about the same age, I think. She may have been a few months older or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15276983\charrsid4274267 younger}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267  but I've always understood that they were the same age. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15276983\charrsid4274267 
I think they were both about twenty six or twenty seven when they married, more or less.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Do you know if she had any job before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes, she was a very good cook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 When she married your father, what work did she do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well, she gave up her work and then when the business came along she helped my father in the business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 When she started helping, were you born by that time, or were you born after?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
I think I must have been born after. I think they'd just about got settled in, or perhaps a few months before. I think a few months before, the business came, from what I've been told.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did she ever have any part-time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, not in those days, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What sort of hours did she work in the business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh well, they were very long hours in those days, you see. I was just thinking the business was open until {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname 
time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 11}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}11 o'clock{\*\xmlclose} at night sometimes, you see, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}
{\xmlattrvalue 11}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}11 o'clock{\*\xmlclose} at night. Yes, and she would be there all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What about Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 The same. There were no half-days in those days. You know, one or two people used to close their shops on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname 
time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 17}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}5 o'clock{\*\xmlclose} on a Thursday, or so which was very unheard of in those days, but the bus
inesses my parents had they were open all the 7 - and on Sundays, I think, until {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 14}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}2 o'clock
{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 So she was out of the home, was she, mostly during that period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, she was a great deal, yes, because we had the first floor and she was in the shop. But
 we did, perhaps, have a - you know, you could get a girl to look after the children in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Did you have living with you - I know you lived in this house with several other families - did you have any relations of your own living with you in your own quarters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did you ever have any lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No. No, we had 3 large rooms on the first floor in Drury Lane when we first started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did your mother ever do any cleaning? I know you said you had a washer-woman and someone in to do 
the rough work, but did she do any cleaning at all, or anything with her hands in the housework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Oh, she was always cooking, and of course, as I say, we had several assistants, and she was cooking and she did a lot of washing and cleaning. I mean, she was always a very, very busy woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 She did washing as well as the washerwoman, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes, she had to, there were 3 big businesses, 3 good businesses. I know my mother used to do quite a lot.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 She did washing for the business, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes. For herself and her family, you know what I mean. Hairdressing, you know, the towels and all those sort of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What about sewing? Did she do anything in the way of making clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, not much, no. I think on one occasion she
 did when we moved to Catford and had a very nice little house there, she did make me two school dresses and that of course I thought was a very great thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 When did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, we lived there - I think we left Drury Lane about 1910 or '11. I was about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10751506\charrsid4274267 ten or eleven}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267  when we got a house. My father thought it would be better for us }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751506\charrsid4274267 three}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267  children to have a house and a little garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I see. I got a bit confused, I thought that when you left Drury Lane you went to Handel Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well, we did go - after Catford we went to Handel St.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 How long were you in Catford, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15276983\charrsid4274267 About four or five years. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
My mother missed the business life in London, she had a nervous breakdown and the doctor did say he thought it better for her to come back to London, where we lived in Handel Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Where were your clothes got from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
They were bought. Sometimes in the market, sometimes Peter Robinson's, places like that. Because in those days we were very careful with clothes. You had your Sun
day clothes and your clothes to go to school in - even with me today, I have my old clothes on now, and when I go to visit I should put on another skirt, and things like that - that's born in me. We weren't so extravagant in those days, because I think pe
ople are very, very extravagant these days. Of course, if you had a dress and you had to wear it a year later you'd let tucks out and all things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 And the same was true of shoes, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes, always had our slippers at home. I do the same these days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Do you remember your father doing anything in the house in the way of helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I think he did, he was a handy man. Not as much as some people would do, but - oh, yes, he did help my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Can you remember anything, any specific thing that he did? Decorating, making fires, cooking, washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, he didn't do any decorating, he wasn't a handyman to that degree, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Can you remember any particular thing you remember him doing in the way of helping in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 W
ell, there was lots of little odds and ends to do. We didn't have electrical things like - a little bit of gardening when we lived at Catford, perhaps, he liked that. And there was, of course, in his business, I think, little plumbing jobs, things like th
at. When he couldn't do them then, of course, they had to get a workman. But I think, perhaps, that some men can't even knock a nail in, he could do things like that, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What about you children, did he do anything for you in the way of putting you to bed, undressing you, telling you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, I don't think so, no, he wasn't that type of man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did he ever take you out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Sometimes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What sort of things, for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well, we'd go to a park for a walk on Sundays. You k
now, a walk in Regents Park was a great occasion, you see. We used to walk there from Drury Lane, or wherever we lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What about you yourself? Did you have any jobs you regularly had to do at home to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes, there was washing my brothers
' socks and all sorts of shopping. I mean, children did quite a lot in those days. Of course, you had to didn't you. I remember my elder brother always had to do his socks and clean his shoes and do all sorts of things. One did a problem tidying up, I kno
w
 I was always on - I'm a very tidy creature, always have been and I think I put it down to ... Mother wasn't quite so ... but I was always tidying up and doing things like that. One had to, I think, in those days. And practicing piano, both of us took pia
no lessons, everybody did, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did you look after your younger brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes. I didn't have any sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What did you do for them, or with them, for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I played with them. They had their toys and my elder brot
her was very clever. We used to work a lot with plasticine in those days, I don't know whether you've ever heard of such a thing, but you could play - it was a sort of soft putty thing and he used to play ... to this day, very artistic little boy he was a
nd he used to make the most fantastic little designs of flowers and things. All sorts of things, he made, could mould out of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15276983\charrsid4274267 this plasticine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 . That I do remember very well, indeed.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Do you remember doing anything for him, like reading to him, for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Not, so much, no. No, I don't think we did so much in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 You had a girl to help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Sometimes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Not always?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No. I don't think it was on quite a permanent basis, though I believe in Catford we did have one then, May E
vans, yes. She was there quite some time with us, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did she live in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
She lived in, yes, 'cos she came from London. Came from a very poor family and so she lived with us and she was very helpful and she was very pleased to be with us, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did she have her meals with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes, yes. She did the housework and helped with the cooking and all sorts of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What used you to call her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 May. Her name was May Evans.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 And you called her May?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What did she call you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
By our Christian names. My mother was always known in the neighbourhood as Madam and I suppose that's what she called her, or Mrs. Cleaver (?) or whatever it was. I think so, but there was no formality.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 She would call your mother, then 'Madam' and she would call her May?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Do you remember dressing your brother, doing anything of that kind for him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, now and again we had to. Oh, yes, I can remember when they were boys keeping still when you dressed them and things 
like that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What about the brothers, did they do anything for you to help you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, they were much younger than me, except annoy me, I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 When you were at school were you expected to go to bed at a set time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I really don'
t know. I didn't think so. We went to bed far later than what the children I think do - as far as I can remember. I can't remember going to bed about half past }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751506\charrsid4274267 six or seven}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 , or half past}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751506\charrsid4274267  seven}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 . Nine or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10751506\charrsid4274267 ten}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 , at least, I'm sure. I can remember standing by th
e window particularly in Drury Lane and looking out at Long Acre, very late at night. And my mother would come up, I think, and 'it's time, quickly pop into bed', or May said why wasn't I in bed. But I know that children in those days were up far later th
an they are today. 'Course, perhaps in these big households, of course, things were different, but the working class people, I think the children were far more lax in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Would you put yourself to bed then, or would anybody else put you to bed when you were a small child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I put myself to bed, or else my mother would have popped upstairs and seen that I was in bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 You had these 3 rooms in Drury Lane, was that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What room were you able to have a bath in? Presumably there was no bathroom at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, there was no bathroom. That would have been in the middle room, in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Was that on a regular day, or days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I think it was mostly on a Friday night, or Saturday night, the end of the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 In some households there was a set day of the week when everyone had clean clothes, was it like that in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes, same at the weekend, after you had your bath, of course, you had them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Now I want to ask you some questions about meals and f
ood. Where, when you were in Drury Lane, I'm sticking to that because you were there a good few years, weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Where did you have your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 In the kitchen, the one kitchen-cum-}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15276983\charrsid4274267 living room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 , and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Well, I think in the front room was ... on occasions when we had visitors and that, you know. If one had ... my aunt and uncle ... christenings or something like that which were big affairs in those days. But I think Mot
her used to do the kitchen table up very, very nicely and it looked always very nice; beautiful table cloth which I have now, still. And we would have ours in the kitchen, I think, then, done up very nicely and perhaps we'd go into the front room which, o
f course, would have a little bed in it, you know, because ... I don't know whether us children, my two brothers and I slept in the one called the front.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 And when ... for example the first meal of the day, breakfast, did you all have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh
, yes, I think yes. I can always remember having egg and bacon or something like that as a youngster. Yes, never .... it would've been unheard of ... we didn't have porridge, that I know, but I'm sure we always had egg and bacon, or something, because Mot
h
er always thought that you should go out with a full stomach it was extremely good ... held those views which I still ... I have porridge nowadays but I still couldn't go without, like my grandchild, without any break-fast or anything. That's something I 
can't do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did you all have it together, as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
I think so, I don't know if perhaps my father would have, perhaps, had his first. But no, I think we would have had it all together on account of going to school. I think we would have had it mo
re or less together, from what I can remember, yes. Egg and bacon, boiled egg or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 And something to drink with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, tea, I think, or coffee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 On a Sunday, would you have anything different for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, I don't think so. We had it when I was married, but that's not in my childhood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What about lunchtime, your {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} meal, or dinner or whatever you called it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did you come home for dinner from school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes, we always had a hot meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 And who would be there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 My mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 She was there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes, always there. Our {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} meal we always had, which I still have now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Could you give me in some detail an example of what she might have cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes. Well, it would be 
either ... perhaps on Sunday it would be a roast, but mostly it would be a braise with lots of vegetables and things like that. I don't think we were very what you'd call a 'sweet' family. My mother didn't make many puddings insofar that she didn't have t
he time to do it, you know, and we had fresh fruit. There was always a nice soup. A good meal, a good {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}
}}midday{\*\xmlclose} meal, that I can always remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What about cheese and pickles, that sort of thing, did you have that at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}}midday{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, I don't think so, no
, no. No, we didn't have that, we had a very good meal, that I do remember as a child. We had very nice stews and all sorts of things that she used to make, because she was a cook. And for tea we used to have, I think, bread and jam, a little bit of cake,
 or sardines now and again, or something like that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What sort of time would that be, that you had your tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I suppose about half past ... I know we came home from school about half past five so we used to have a little tea ... tea, and p
erhaps one or two of the poorer children upstairs come down and have a little tea with us, you know. There was a big family living up there, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751506\charrsid4274267 twelve}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267  children, and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 And what about your mother, did she sit down with you for lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
I think so, oh, yes, yes. Or else May Evans, perhaps, would have been there a little bit. I don't know if she came in the evening for a couple of hours. But I think my mother would be there, oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 And your father, what about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well, he would come up if he wasn't too busy, you see, yes, but he would have tea, also.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Was that the last refreshment or food you had in the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, I think .... In those days I think one always used to have a little bit of supper. Perhaps it was a sausage
 or something like that we used to have, and perhaps cheese and pickle in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What sort of time would that have been, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 About 9 or 10, I suppose. I know it must have been quite late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I remember you said that your mother sent out 
a joint to the baking house sometimes, and the same was true of a cake? She might make a cake and do that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes, those large cakes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did she bake any bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did she make any jam or do any bottling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, no, not in town, she 
couldn't do that, no. Although I've ... yes, towards the end she used to make some lovely plum jam and damson jam. Now that I do remember because they used to be scoffed off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What about wine making or brewing, that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 When you were a child, do you remember any livestock being kept at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, well, my father used to have a pussy - a cat in the shop he was very fond of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 But there was nothing kept for supplying with food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, no, we had nowhere, no room, in any case.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I just wondered if in Catford, perhaps, you'd had hens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, we hadn't take that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 About how many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well, I suppose it would be more ... nearly every day, because we were in business, we weren't quite ... 
very poor people, you see. But I think more or less every day. I don't think we had ... there again, fish would come into it. Or she'd make nice dumplings with liver in it, or something like that, as far as I can remember, to make a change. But more or le
ss it was ... or sausage, perhaps, you know, you could buy sausages, have sausage and something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Was your mother and father's food different from you and your brothers' in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Now, about manners and behaviour at meals; were you allowed to talk during a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Oh, I think so. Our family wasn't quite as strict, being a business family, you see, I don't think you could be quite as strict as some people were. Although, looking back and seeing some of the children of today, my frie
nds that I go to, I find them very ill-mannered today, which of course, my mother or my father with a look with big black eyes at us it would have been quite sufficient for us to have behaved ourselves. Even if we'd have thought of doing otherwise.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 W
hat about the choice of food? Say your mother cooked the dinner, could you choose which parts of it, for example you would like to eat and which you wouldn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well, we all have our dislikes, of course. My younger brother couldn't eat onion and that so
rt of thing. I could never eat butter, that's one thing in my life I could never ... but I don't think ... I think more or less my mother knew that ... what we all generally liked. Of course, some liked this a little bit more than others, or sometimes ...

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 But you weren't forced to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, but I must say my mother didn't encourage us to be too finicky. What was there, was there and ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 And suppose you accepted a helping of something and you left some uneaten on the plate, what would her attitude be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Well, you know, my mother would give a little lecture to say that there were many poor children there who would have liked it, and that sort of thing. So one was encouraged to eat up one's food, I must say that. I don'
t think on the whole ... unless one wasn't well. My brothers were always ailing or they had ... boys are a little bit difficult, perhaps they would have left a little bit, but on the whole we weren't encouraged to leave a lot of food ... to leave anything
 like that. We were always told to eat it up, get big, or whatever the case may be.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4274267  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751506\charrsid4274267 S}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 it up straight. Mum always used to say I should become round-shouldered if I was like that. Always threatened with being very round-shouldered and nobody would look at your
. So you were encouraged to sit up straight and I can always remember my mother looking and saying, 'come on, now, sit up straight. What's the sense bending over like that, sit up straight'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 But you could ask for things, you were saying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes, certainly, yes. It wasn't a Victorian household quite like that. Oh, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Could you bring toys or books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What about leaving the table? At what stage in the meal were you allowed to leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Well, I don't think perhaps we could just ask. From what I can remember as you finished your meal, then I think ... yes, I think Mother would have said 'you can go, now'. Of course, one didn't have a large house, we were just business people, just
 ... we could go to the other side of the room or so and play with our toys or do something like that. I think, perhaps if there were visitors, an aunt and uncle were there and they wanted to talk, I think my mother would say, 'well, you can go now, we're
 having a little talk now. Go downstairs' ... nice where you could play in the street in front of there, or wherever you wanted to.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Was Grace ever said at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I think my Mother used to. I don't think it was regular, but I think on the whole mo
re times than not, she used to say ... yes. It wasn't such a formality, perhaps as some plays, or some people you see in those days. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Can you remember anything else about manners and meals, at mealtimes and this sort of thing that she used to think important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Well, as I say now, looking back at some of my friends now I find them very, very ill-mannered indeed. They jump up and they leave the table and they do all this, that and the other. Their parents correct them because the dear children mus
tn't be frustrated these days and the children do as they please. And of course, I'm old-fashioned - aunty's old-fashioned. But no, no, there wasn't too formalities, but as I say we were well behaved and if we hadn't've been my mother, as I say, would jus
t look at us and it would be quite sufficient, even if we had friends there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Was she an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes, yes. A most charming woman, she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 If you were worried about something, was she the sort of person you could tell your worries to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
I think so, although of course, they were in business, both of them and that makes a great deal of difference, you see. My mother wasn't always with us all of the time, you know what I mean. And business was business and they had their pro
blems, I suppose. I think I did, but I don't think I was perhaps as close to my mother as some daughters are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Were you closer to your mother than to your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, to my mother, definitely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Was she the sort of person who showed affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes, she was very fond of us children, especially the two boys in any case, you know. She was very fond of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, with respect, of course, they were Mamma and Papa, and that
 was that. There was none of your 'Mum' and 'Dad' larks, or anything, you know, that you see these days. No, there was a little bit of ... Mamma was there, and Papa, and that was that and you called them such. You didn't call them 'the old girl' or 'the o
ld boy' which ... or by their Christian names, which I think is dreadful.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 And did they bring you up to behave in a certain way towards your brothers? Do you remember how they felt you should ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I was the eldest and I was supposed to set them a good example, which was always drummed down one's throat, in any case.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 If, say, another child hit you or bullied you in any way, what would their attitude be? Did they say you should hit back, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No. No, no, my mother always used to say that
's not the way to stop a quarrel. 'you mustn't do that, no, no.' Perhaps, playing in the street, you know, and they'd come home and say 'So-and-so hit me', well then you wasn't encouraged to hit back, to prolong the quarrel and that sort of thing. You kno
w, she was rather a peace-loving person. No, we weren't encouraged to stand up too much for ourselves, no, no. On the contrary, we were more encouraged to give in a little bit, you see, which I think just as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did your parents have certain hopes and expectations for their children, do you think? The kind of people they'd like them to grow up to be?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Oh, yes, I think they had great aspirations, but the War came, you see, the First World War, and that's quite another story which upset all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
What sort of hopes do you think they had for you as people, and in your future life? What sort of people do you think they wanted you to grow up to be? In character, for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well, I don't know .... I went to a trade school and to
 another high school and I suppose she had great hopes for me, but they were dashed to the ground. And of course, my elder brother was a very, very clever boy. He certainly made a great name for himself in business and is certainly a rich man now, and thr
o
ugh his own efforts. I think both his parents had they been alive would have been very pleased with his achievements in later life, but they didn't live to see. They didn't live to be very old. No, I think they had ambitions for one; I expect Mother thoug
h
t, perhaps, of me making a desirable nice marriage, or something like that, you know. But I think the chief thing was that as long as you could keep a home running and that sort of thing, cooking, cleaning, things like that which was a great thing in thos
e days, you know. You were more of less encouraged that way, you know, to be tidy and clean and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What were the sort of things they brought you up to consider important in life, then? To be tidy, to be clean...?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes. And
 good principles, you know, we were a very patriotic ... a very ... family that was brought up to love our country and that sort of thing, and any of these people who were against the country in those days, you know, my parents could never understand it i
n
 a way. They thought that everything was very well as it was, and perhaps the revolutionaries or the type of things which go on today I think they would have been terrified, would have been very sad. The chief aim was to do your best in life, to be honest
,
 of course, was the great principle in life. My mother was a great Christian, in any case. And of course, the great thing was to do your best in life and the best to your fellow creatures. We were brought up to do ... as I say, anybody punched you on the 
face you mustn't punch back, that wasn't my parents' attitude. You'd try to forgive them, or not to aggravate them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 And I remember all the things you were telling Sloane about how she helped people, too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, she was, she was a very fine Christian 
person. I remember her example, I mean now it's something for me to look back on, what a wonderful woman she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Would you say that these ideas you got, about what was right, would you say that you got them more from one parent than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I
 should think more from my mother. My father was more on the distant side, I don't know quite how to explain it, but being more on the business side and he ... as I say, I ... when my father died I was sorry, but when my mother died sort of the end of the
 world had come for me. I lost my greatest friend, you see. Even when my husband died it never had such an impact on me as when my mother died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Now, in those days, in the home, did you have birthday parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well, not big parties 'cos we were in business, but we did have some of the children from upstairs. Oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did you have any present-giving at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes, we had one or two presents. Oh, yes. I mean not these expensive presents one has today, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What about Christmas Day, how was that kept?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Oh, that would have been kept up very nicely, indeed. We always had a beautiful real Christmas tree, which I still have today every Christmas, a real tree. And ... oh, Christmas ... my mother had a really nice voice and
 we all, after Christmas we all sang the lovely Christmas Carols. My mother sang very, very nicely. And of course, in those days you entertained yourself, you see. Well, of course, after Christmas tea which was always a very nice affair, then of course, m
y
 mother would sing and my father would sing and we children were brought up to do our little party piece, whatever it may be, you know. And it was a very, very pleasant affair and everybody joined in. We'd have my aunt and uncle, perhaps would come round,
 
and my little cousin and ... not that we had many relations. And Christmas was, of course, ... Mother being a Christian, I think very often she went to Church on Christmas morning and so arranged her dinner that she could go and then come home and I think
 
it was a bit of a late .... I think my father opened his business on Christmas morning. Yes, I'm sure he did for an hour or two. I know my mother would come home with ... and so we'd have dinner a little bit late. Of course it was always a very big dinner
 in those days, very pleasant family affair.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Was your father a Church-goer, too, or did he not go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, no, not like Mother, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 On Christmas Day did you go out at all, as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, I don't think we ever did, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 You say you used to play the piano, did you have a piano in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Not in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname Street}}Drury Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, not 'till we got to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname Street}}Handel St{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What about any other musical instruments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, there was no other, no. Oh, a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15276983\charrsid4274267 zither}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 , I had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15276983\charrsid4274267 zither}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 , but I didn't play it very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 You said your mother used to sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did she just sing unaccompanied, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did the rest of you sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes, we all joined in 'cos we knew all the Carols.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Do you remember your mother and father reading? I know they didn't have a lot of time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
No, I don't think so. No. I think my father used to get the French papers sent over, or get a French paper. Though they were both English my Mother could speak French and Italian and German and had a great insigh
t into Spanish, but they were linguists, both of them and of course, as I said, they wanted to hold a little discussion which we children didn't have, they could either speak in German or French or Italian, something like that, and I know they had a littl
e
 literature of that type of thing would come in, now and again. They had a lot of friends, one or two Italians would come in, and French people would come in and there'd be very excited arguments which we didn't understand, political arguments, which I th
ink was very, very interesting. Must have been, in any case. It was that type of household, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Were there a lot of people coming in, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I don't say a lot of people, but we had one or two French people, a very nice French gentleman and a 
lady who lived in Charlotte St., well, they used to come in now and again, perhaps on a Sunday walk and pop in and see us, and perhaps have a cup of coffee or a little light wine drink, I think, from what I can remember, and they would have a little argum
e
nt in French about some French political subject. And of course, my parents liked it, they could practice their French, so to speak, keep a little 'in'. And these French people also spoke Italian. So of course, in those days, on a Sunday evening it was ve
ry pleasant, I mean for them my mother was always pleased when Monsieur }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
 Madame Simone used to come down to see them 'cos they could discuss things in Paris which ... they'd both been and lived for a couple of years, you see. My mother had lived there. My mother had a very good job as a cook in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname City}}Paris{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Is that where she learnt her French?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Yes, and they kept it up. And of course, they went over there primarily to learn French, you see. And my father. They learnt Italian ... some Italian people, friends they knew in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname 
Street}}Handel St.{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, not far from here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 When you moved to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname Street}}Handel St.{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 they learnt it there, did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, I don't say they learnt it in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname Street}}Handel St.{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}, but they learnt it from ... before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Before they lived there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Do you ever remember a funeral in the family when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No. No, 'cos my grandparents, they died abroad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Do you remember going on any outings with your parents? I remember you said sometimes you used to go to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname 
place}}Brighton{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What about other outings, sort of day outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, no, I don't ... Oh, yes, I think they liked to go once or twice during the summer to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}
Epping Forest{\*\xmlclose}. That was a great occasion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 And they would go together, would they? They'd be able to go away together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes, yes. Oh, yes, that was quite an occasion. Or now and then go to Hampstead, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Were you taken out visiting friends and neighbours? And relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Now and again but as I say we didn't really have so many ... but they didn't really have the time, really, to go visiting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Were you ever taken out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes, yes, yes. Oh, yes, round to Bourne }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15276983\charrsid4274267 Hollingsworth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267  and places like that; Peter Robinson}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10751506\charrsid4274267 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 s. But not very often because as I say ... first of all you didn't want so man
y clothes, and that sort of thing. And then perhaps, now and again you had ... my mother knew a dressmaker which would make her a dress occasionally which, as I say, you kept clothes for years and years in those days. And I would have a dress made. But yo
u did go occasionally shopping, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 When your parents weren't at work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Well, they'd do a bit of reading, perhaps. Of course, there was always something to do in the shop, they'd always have plenty of little odds and ends to do down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 The shop where your mother and father worked, was that always attached to where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well, no, only so far as {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname Street}}Drury Lane{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} and then when we moved to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname Street}}Handel St.{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, of course, that was away from the shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 So when you moved to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname Street}}Handel St.{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 did you see less of your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Well, she didn't ... my younger brother was born and then she gave up the shop. My father had another business and they put a manager in there 'cos my mother couldn't cope.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Do you remember when your youngest brother was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 How did your mother manage then, 'cos babies were born at home then, weren't they? Do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes, the babies ... my two brothers were born at home. Dr. Ryan lived next door, and I think she had
 a midwife in to help her, I can remember that. Hot water business, and so forth. I was about 8 then, when the last baby came. Well, she managed somehow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Do you remember her getting any help from neighbours or relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, I don't think the nei
ghbours so much, no. I don't know. No, I don't think ... sort of ... a person who didn't give in so much. After the birth ... as soon as she could get up after the birth she got up and did her work. My father and myself ... I never give in. I think she wa
s the same type of person.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
I know they went to a pantomime at Christmas and then they did - now and again she had ticket or would go to a theatre, but it was an occasion, not as much ... but not to g
o out dining or anything like this. One or two ... perhaps an anniversary they went to, that lovely }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751506\charrsid4274267 cascade}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
 which in those days which was a very great occasion, but we didn't go. I think my mother and father and perhaps cousin, perhaps, a friend they had over once from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname country-region}}
America{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15276983\charrsid4274267 somewhere}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
. They went out to an occasional ... Once or twice they may have gone to a little restaurant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751506\charrsid4274267  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
to have a little supper on a Sunday evening; perhaps I would be taken, and that was that, but it wasn't a usual thing, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What about clubs? Did your father belong to any clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 And did he go to pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Now and again, yes, now and again he'd go to one. But, .... no, they'd have their little wine or something like that. But he would go now and again on business, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did he take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Or watch sport, or go to the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Well, there wasn't so much sport ... any football in those days, from what I can remember or football results, and he was in business all the time, so
 no, he didn't go. And there was no television or anything like that to watch, you see, or cinemas. They didn't come 'till rather later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did they belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, no, they didn't go in for anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did they go to any evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I suppose many evenings they were working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well mostly, because as I say, the shops would be open until quite }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751506\charrsid4274267 
ten or eleven}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 . Later I think they closed a bit ... but up to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10751506\charrsid4274267 F}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 irst World War, at Newport Court when he had that business there I can ... oh, yes, it was quite 9 o'clock before ... and he couldn't do anything else then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Was there one of your brothers you felt particularly close to, or did you feel the same about both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well, I think the old
er one, the one who's alive now. I think we always had more in common than the younger one. He was more his mother's baby, so to speak.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 But how would you say you got on with them on the whole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, quite well. Oh, yes, we were brought .... I was t
he elder of the family and even my elder brother today regards me ... he always comes and asks my advice, you know. You had that little thing ... you were brought up with it, you know, you respected your sisters. Oh, yes, there was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 When you were a little child and living in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname Street}}Drury Lane
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and a bit older, too, who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well, the children round about, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did your parents have any particular views on who you should or should not play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, well, there were one o
r two naughty children about and we were told ... Mother told us not to play with so-and-so because we would pick up their bad ways, or whatever the case may be. I know one point of having a girl, she used to take us, generally when we came in after schoo
l, to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname City}}Lincoln{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}'s Inn Fields, we were taken. I spent a lot of my childhood in those lovely fields. I go round now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 But were you allowed to play in the street as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes. We had nowhere else to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What about being allowed to get dirty when you played? Were you allowed to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well, to a point, yes, but ... you know, not too bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did you belong to any youth clubs or organizations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, no. Except to the Church, you know, went the Band of Hope and Sunday School in the morning and I think ... something to do with 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname PlaceName}}Holy{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname PlaceName}}Trinity{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname PlaceType}}Church{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, Kingsway. I think we used to go on one or two little sessions round there. I think we did that, but not to a youth club as such.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 How did you spend your free time when you were a schoolgirl? Did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Yes, I think I used to do needlework and embroidery. Mother used to get me linen, and that, and I used to do drawn-threadwork. I've one or two bits still left now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What about collecting, did you collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No. One
 used to collect those cigarette cards, you know, and have albums of that. We were ... I can remember making nice big scrapbooks. Of course, when you move you get rid of that. But, you know, nice pictures, and that. They used to be rather large scrap book
s and they would be very interesting. Perhaps something would be in a paper, a nice picture and you'd cut them out, and you'd look at them. Oh, yes, yes, I did have that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What about having a bicycle, did you have a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did you take part in any sport at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
No, I don't think, particularly. I wasn't ... well, I didn't really like sport, I'm not that type of a child. I used to go in those ... you know, our school days and we used to run in a ... egg and spoon race, or any
thing like that, but was never good at it. No, I wasn't one for ... I took up a little bit of tennis, I think. Oh, roller skating was ... I suppose that was my biggest sport.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Where would you do that, in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 In the street, yes. Down into dear Father Thomas, down those little streets by the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}Strand
{\*\xmlclose}. I'd go down {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname country-region}}Sussex{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and we used to take our skates down there, one or two }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10751506\charrsid4274267 our}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267  choir boys and a party of us would go and skate down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did you go to any theatres, or concerts or music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 We used to ... we had the fortune in Handel St. ... a neighbour upstairs who was a celebrated }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15276983\charrsid4274267 vio}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 linist and she used to get a lot of tickets to Queen's Hall and the A}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15276983\charrsid4274267 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 olian Hall and the Wigmore Hall,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15276983\charrsid4274267  and I suppose I was quite }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 a nice little girl and 
I used to go with her. And once or twice I know I went on the platform at Wigmore Hall and turned her music over for her. But I did go to some very nice concerts. In those days we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I remember you saying to Miss Sloane that you used to buy little penny fairy books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Was that money that your parents gave you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes. We didn't do any little jobs or anything like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 You didn't have little jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did your parents give you the money regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, I
 don't think we had a regular pocket money, no. No, we wanted the little ... one of these little fairytale books which were always ... yes, I used to look forward to that, every Friday they used to come out. They were a penny. Oh, yes, we had that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 And she would give you the money for that, specially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes, and a penny or a halfpenny for sweets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 When you went to your first job in Bourne }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267  Hollingsworth, was that the very first job you'd ever had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes, I'd come from the trade school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 You'd never earned money before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What exactly were you doing in that work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I was in millinery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What were the hours when you first started there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Nine, 'till 6 or 7, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Including Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes. I knew I used to come home to dinner, which is quite a long way from Bourne's to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname Street}}Handel St.{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and I walked there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What were you paid, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 About 15/- a week. That was, like, a First Hand. The second were lower down, about 12/6d. I think, but I think it was 15/- a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Do you remember if at that time you thought that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
I don't think I particularly ... I think there's a better ... than some a system, you know, catching ... you used to get about 10/- or something like that. You see, I was qualified.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 It was a lot of money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes, 15/- was. And then I think I went up to 17/6, or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 When you got this money, did you give any to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 How much would you give her?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I suppose it would be about 10/- or more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 And the rest, what did you spend that on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well I suppose, buy a few clothes and little things like that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 You were responsible for your own clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well, I don't think completely, as far a
s I can remember. Just had a little pocket money, as I say one didn't ... there weren't the things to ... I know I saved up for a little coat at Bourne }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267  Hollingsworth every week, but, no, one didn't have so much money to spend at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Do you think you would have liked to do any other work besides millinery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well, no, that was my one ambition, to be a milliner. I always wanted to be a milliner, I don't know why, as a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Have you always done work of that kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well, I've always done s
ewing, afterwards, I'm now a tailoress. I've been a tailoress since I married my husband, since 1923. I've worked in the West End of London.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Up to this time in 1918, did you belong to any trade union or professional organizations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 No, never done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests, or that there was a difference, a conflict between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I don't know. I don't think one thought about it quite so much. I know there was all this about the suffragettes and the ema
ncipation of women which there were but I didn't really think so much about, but ... No, looking back I don't think an ordinary person like myself ... ordinary girl like myself, perhaps, wasn't so divided. I don't know. I know you knew there were rich peo
p
le there and perhaps one envied the people who had all this, that and the other, but I don't think there was quite that forceful envious that there is today, you know. People do lots of things to get it these days, you know. I suppose ... now, as I say, t
h
ese days if you're good at it you can earn a lot ... if I wanted to I could earn a lot of money at my trade, you see, because insofar ... there's not the people that do my certain type of work, you see. In those days there wasn't that demand, there wasn't
 that sort of thing, you see, so of course, you couldn't do ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 And what about among the working people themselves, did you feel there was a division of interests among them, or did you think ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes, I think there was a lot of ignorance. There's a lot of ignorance now, for that matter, more so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 But the trained people, you know, the skilled people like yourself who had a trade and the others, did you feel there was a big ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, there was jealousy, they were pretty ... even in Bour
ne's, you know, the first madam, the head milliner and even her big hand, that that, to this day when I go I think that she sort of ruled with a terror, you know. You know, you did have to respect her. Of course, that's to be ... I think even now, today, 
perhaps my boss ... I'm still nervous now in case I don't do my work right and they say, 'well, no need for you to worry', but it's part of my makeup.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Would you say that going to work fulltime changed your attitude to life in any way? Make any differen
ce to you as a person, the way you looked at things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well, you know it gave you ... you were more independent, weren't you? You earned your own money. You were independent, oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did you come into contact with types of people and life that you hadn't before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Oh, yes, I think so. Yes, living in that part of the world one came into contact with one or two rather loose people, perhaps, which you would meet in those days, you know. Ladies of easy virtue, you know, you may have envied them a li
ttle bit, seeing their clothes and that sort of thing. You were young, you know, you really didn't know what they were there ... until you were told one day and of course ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 You hadn't come into contact with that type of person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Not before, no, 
but I did know a lady who owned a house in Marchmont St. and on the one occasion I did used to go round and sort of help her a little bit - I don't know why, she was a friend of my mother's - and she had quite a few of these ladies there and, of course, i
t did open my eyes considerably, you know. You saw the other side of life, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 You mean the ladies were lodging at her house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes, and of course, kept on their other business as well. You closed your eyes to that ... the police closed their e
yes to that, what was taking place, but nevertheless it took place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
When you were working did you feel it changed your relationship with your parents and brothers at all? You said you felt more independent, in any other way did it make you change?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way? You mentioned doing a bit of needlework.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 One didn't have so much freedom, you worked 'till rather ... and by the time you came home I suppose you were tired, and s
ummertime what would you do? You'd have your tea and then either go for a walk around the park, or to Lincoln's Inn Fields and places, and hear the bands and meet your friends, and ...
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did you make any new friends? Boys, or girls at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes, one did make a few friends, yes. Indeed so, one did make a few friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Where did you meet them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Oh, that ... in those days, we got attached to the Kingsway Hall and my mother went there, became a member there and of course, they had very
 nice social meetings there where my brothers went, and that and that opened up another ... quite another different aspect of things, you know. It was very pleasant indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did you meet new people there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes, indeed so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Of your own age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did you have any special, particular friends, either boys or girls, at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes, I did have one or two friends, of course, one or two boyfriends, but I was never much one for boys, I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did you go out with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 We went out more as a little party of us, you know, round the park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Going for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Going for walks, yes, we were great }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15276983\charrsid4274267 walker}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267  in those days. I can remember coming out of Church in Kingsway and walking right down through to the East E
nd of London. You wouldn't dream of having bus for a penny or whatever it may have been, or so, and we walk right from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15276983\charrsid4274267 Kingsway}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
 right to Aldgate, you know and explore all round the City. You did a lot more exploring in those days. I know {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} very well, 
only on account of my youth, you see. Coming from Church and going round all different parts of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 You were lucky to have that experience of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes, I know {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 very well. Of course, it's changed dreadfully and of course, these days I can now walk, if I go for a walk I can take a taxi back, which is still ... I've got the time to do these things, but can't do it any more. But {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname 
place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, of course, ... but that was our ... one of our chief things. I had friends at St. Clement Dane's Ch
urch and we'd meet one or two more friends from there after the ... and then we'd go for lovely walks in the City of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and in those days ...
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 At that time you did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 In those days, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 And these friends - your boyfriends, you said you had a few - did your parents meet them, did they like to know who you were going with?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Oh, I think so. Oh, yes, they knew from a ... Oh, yes. They didn't come to the house, they couldn't ... but Mother always knew who we were going ... either this 
or the other, you were going with Florrie Condor and a few other little friends, you know, you were going for a walk after you came from Church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Did they expect to know where you were and what your movements were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, more or less, oh, yes. You wasn't allowed to come in too late, or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Were there certain fixed times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
I don't say there were certain fixed times, no, I don't think so, no. But on the other hand you wouldn't, perhaps, have gone out like some youngsters today and perhaps walking all hours of the night. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15276983\charrsid4274267 And if your parents asked you, you just say 'well, so what?', which is the answer for everything these days, anyway.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 You mentioned the French couple in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname Street}}Charlotte St.
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, would they just drop in unannounced?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes, yes. There was nothing, formality, about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What about formal entertaining, say to a meal, or that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, there were occasions when one did used to have one or two ... specially when we used to live at Catford, then of cou
rse ... one or two of my father's business friends, and that, and we had a nice }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15276983\charrsid4274267 dining room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
 and a nice house. And of course, then Mother did entertain very nicely and things were done very ... But while you're in business, you know, things had to be a little bit more ... you know, not quite ... you didn't have the time to ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 In Catford, what sort of people, for example, would come? Were they relations, or friends, or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well, more ... friends that one knows and didn't have time, when you
're in business in London ... or the space to entertain, would come and see you on a Saturday and Sunday, for tea, chiefly, and once or twice they may come for the day. Chiefly for tea and supper in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What about neighbours? I know you lived
 very close to neighbours, of course, 'cos you shared these houses and your mother, I seem to remember did a lot to help these people, lending them the gas and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well, they were very, very poor people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Was there any kind of social activity with the neighbours, at all? Did you have a cup of tea with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Oh, no, no. The children ... there was a family of twelve on the top, I remember, very nicely behaved children. How that woman managed with the children I shall never know, 
but Rosie and two or three of the girlies would come down very often and have tea, which was a great treat for them. And I remember my mother always ... if we didn't eat Mother used to say 'well you can go up to the Johnson's, they have nothing up there',
 
or something like that. But however, one did have friends in, yes. But to have the big parties, I think, which children have now, they bring a present and have a big children's party, I don't think it was prevalent in those ... of course, in the real midd
le class people, of course, they did it, but we were just a little cut above the ordinary working class, used to have two or three friends in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 You said you were a little bit above the ordinary class, what sort of people were in that same class with you at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well, I suppose business people, people who had shops, business people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What were the other classes at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Well, either the very poor people, as I say, or ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Like the family upstairs, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Like the famil
y upstairs, and all around one. People lived in one room in those days, you see, there were so many families in that one large house, they just had one room with two or three children. Very respectable, very nice people that just couldn't help themselves,
 very nice people indeed. My mother didn't mind as long as they were what we call decent people, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 You said people used to call your mother Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What did they call your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I don't think they saw so much of him, he was rather a retiring, reserved sort of man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Do you remember people showing respect to your parents, say, by }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15276983\charrsid4274267 curtseying}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 , or touching caps?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, no, no. Nothing like that at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Were you brought up to treat people of one type differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Well, you had to have respect. Say, for instance with teachers, of course, we were always brought up to have great respect for the teachers, I mean, they were - and I agree with it, I hold that view still - that one was ... and perh
aps a doctor, Dr. Ryan, would come and see my mother in a professional ... or just as a friend at different times, you did have respect for them, far more than I think a lot of modern people have today for people like that of the professional classes. I t
hink you were taught to ... you were brought up that way, and I have today... hold still the same views on that, I mean to say, I ... doctors, or if I come into contact ... or with teachers, in particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Do you remember hearing at that time some families, say, called 'rough I and others 'respectable'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Oh, yes. Well, there were some very rough and common people about. I mean, there really were, and there are today, too. But I mean, there were in those days, round Covent Garden, and that, various o
f them ... Covent Garden porters and ... and some of the Drury Lane people, you know, some of them very, very rough, indeed. But then, of course, you were taught not to mix with them and even today, even round here, there are lots of very rough children i
n Council flats. But in those days, of course, people ... they were rough, there was just that little....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 At that time to you ever remember hearing anybody described as 'a real gentleman', or 'a real lady'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 What sort of ... what do you think people would mean if they'd say 'she's a real lady' at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 
Well, they would just have a little of .... superior, they had just that something. I can remember one or two very, very nice people, real ladies. I mean, you couldn't ima
gine them doing anything wrong, and they had that bearing with them, which is also either born in them or bred in them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Would it have any connection with money, would you say, that sort of person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 I don't think ... no, no. We had a very charming woman in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname Street}}
Drury Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, a Miss Crudge, and she was a skirt-maker now I come to think of it, in the Haymarket. There was something very noble about that woman. She was a spinster. But my mother held her in the greatest respect and so did we children, we would 
no more thought of being rude or anything, and if she was coming on the stairs or whatever the case may be, she had a command. And yet she was charming and sweet to the children. Now and again perhaps she'd give us a little book, or have a little talk wit
h
 us. But there was something about her and yet she was only just a person who earned ... only just an ordinary skirtmaker, an ordinary woman ... seamstress, in those days, but she commanded a little bit of respect, I don't know what it was. She was a lady
. We called her that. My friends called her that. I thought it was very, very nice.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3636049 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Do you think at that time it was easy to move from one class of people to another? Was it possible for people to move up and down, you know?

\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s15\qj \fi-490\li518\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin518\itap0\pararsid3636049 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12460854 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5243694\charrsid4274267 Oh, I think so, once 
one ... one noticed it moved or went even to see friends at Golders Green, or anything like that, there certainly was. Oh, there were still that class, it's no use saying you can lump people altogether, even though they're trying to, you can't. I can reme
mber, even when we went to Catford, the people next door were very, very nice people, but there was that something...
\par }}